What you need to know:

Publicly, organisers are still adamant the Games can go ahead, and say they can be held safely even if the virus is not under control by the time the flame is lit on July 23However, with much of the world still paralysed by Covid-19, and Tokyo under a state of emergency, the doubting voices are growing louderTokyo 2020 chiefs say another postponement is "absolutely impossible", meaning the Games will be cancelled if they cannot go ahead this year